trans-unit.source: Computes a 2-D atrous convolution, also known as convolution with holes or dilated convolution, given 4-D value and filters tensors. If the rate parameter is equal to one, it performs regular 2-D convolution. If the rate parameter is greater than one, it performs convolution with holes, sampling the input values every rate pixels in the height and width dimensions. This is equivalent to convolving the input with a set of upsampled filters, produced by inserting rate - 1 zeros between two consecutive values of the filters along the height and width dimensions, hence the name atrous convolution or convolution with holes (the French word trous means holes in English).
trans-unit.target: 在给定4-D value ，计算2-D原子卷积（也称为带孔卷积或膨胀卷积）并 filters 张量。如果 rate 参数等于1，则执行常规的2D卷积。如果 rate 参数大于1，则会对孔进行卷积，并在 height 和 width 尺寸中的每个 rate 像素处采样输入值。这等效于将输入与一组上采样的滤波器进行卷积，这是通过在沿 height 和 width 两个连续的滤波器值之间插入 rate - 1 零而产生的 尺寸，因此命名为atrous卷积或带孔卷积（法语单词trous表示英语中的孔）。
